Date: Tue 14 Aug 2001 07:48:17 -0500
From: Danny Dutton <dwdutton@cvm.tamu.edu>
Source: Dallas Morning News, Tue 14 Aug 2001 [edited

Viral Encephalitis Cases in Louisiana now Total 16
--------------------------------------------------
MONROE: As many as 16 patients in Ouachita Parish in Louisiana have
mosquito-borne encephalitis or symptoms of the disease as state officials
await test results. Meanwhile, a blue jay found in suburban New Orleans
appears to have tested positive for the potentially deadly West Nile virus,
Dr. Raoult Ratard, the state epidemiologist, said on Mon 13 Aug 2001.
Dr. Ratard said that 7 patients in Monroe had tested positive for a form of
encephalitis linked to [caused by either West Nile virus or St. Louis
encephalitis virus.
--
